Age-Hardening/Precipitation strengthening

    Consider a phase diagram example of Al - 2wt% Cu

    If alloy cooled slowly:
        expect formation of theta precipitates when cooled from alpha region
    to control/improve the strength of alloy:
        (1)Solution treatment
            heat alloy to single phase region (T_sol) which is only alpha
        (2)Quench from alpha region
            rapidly cool metal
            material is super saturated alpha(more than equilibrium)
            no theta precipitates
        (3)Age-Hardening
            heat materail for a specific temp and time(T_age, t_age)
            precipitates of theta form and grow (max amount of theta is given by lever rule)

            what about properties?
                plot of hardness vs log(time)

                optium size/distribution leads to peak aging
